      "content": "Yes, that is a perfectly valid observation, as the term \"fake news\" has become a powerful rhetorical shield. It is frequently deployed by politicians to discredit legitimate investigative journalism or dissenting opinions without having to address the substance of the critique. This usage weaponizes the concept itself, turning it into a catch-all dismissal for any unfavorable information. Therefore, the term has become a tool of deflection as much as it is a descriptor of falsehood.",
